### The Upstream Sync Principle

The `commons/` directory is **upstream, read-only**. When the OS template evolves — new manifests, updated definitions, refined specifications — the changes arrive via upstream sync. Your job: notice what changed. Re-read the changed documents. Adapt your understanding. The commons definition in `the-commons.md` is the anchor — everything else orbits around it.

